{"000-section": {"000-title": "Aajeevika Grameen Express Yojana (AGEY) in Punjab \u2013 Interest Free Loans for SHGs"}, "001-section": {"000-title": "Aajeevika Grameen Express Yojana (AGEY) to be launched in Punjab on 2 Oct 2018 to provide interest-free loans upto Rs. 6 lakhs to members of self help groups (SHGs) for purchase of vehicles under Deendayal Antyodaya Yojana - National Rural Livelihood Mission (DAY-NRLM), beneficiaries of Mahatma Gandhi Sarbat Vikas Yojana (MGSVY) will also be facilitated"}, "002-section": {"000-title": "Punjab Aajeevika Grameen Express Yojana (AGEY)", "001-normal": "The scheme Aajeevika Grameen Express Yojana is being launched under the National Rural Livelihood Mission to benefit 123 self help group families. The community investment fund (CIF) provided to community based organization (CBOs) under DAY-NRLM will be utilized in order to support SHG members in this livelihoods initiative. SHG beneficiaries will be provided an interest free loan by the CBO upto Rs.6.50 lakh for purchase of the vehicle.", "002-normal": "Alternatively, it is also proposed that CBO will own the vehicle and lease it to an SHG member to operate the vehicle and pay lease rental to the CBO. This initiative is going to be launched as a pilot project in 6 blocks from FY 2018-19 to 2020-21.", "003-normal": "All the SHG members who operates these vehicles must ensure that he / she must be operating the vehicle with necessary requirements like valid permit, road tax permit, valid insurance policy. SHG members will run these vehicles on approved routes at pre-determined frequency agreed upon by CBO and SHG operator on the basis of financial viability and need for transport link.", "004-normal": "All vehicles under Aajeevika Grameen Express Yojana (AGEY) scheme shall have a defined colour code. These vehicles would also carry AGEY branding to ensure their identity and avoid diversion to other routes."}, "003-section": {"000-title": "Facilitation of Mahatma Gandhi Sarbat Vikas Yojna (MGSVY) Beneficiaries", "001-normal": "On 2nd October 2018, CM will inaugurate a state-level mega camp to facilitate the beneficiaries of the Mahatma Gandhi Sarbat Vikas Yojna (MGSVY). As per the issued directions, 90 mega camps will be organized at sub-divisional levels across the state.", "002-normal": "These camps will ensure that no deserving and eligible beneficiary is deprived of the benefits of welfare schemes started under MGSVY. Till date, around 27 lakh applications have been received under MGSVY, out of which around 9 lakh beneficiaries are found to be eligible."}}